tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Quantum_Communication_Events (
    event_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    event_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    event_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    sender_address VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    receiver_address VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    quantum_protocol VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_events (
	event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	event_date DATE,
	communication_type VARCHAR(50),
	source_node VARCHAR(50),
	destination_node VARCHAR(50),
	message_content TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_message_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  message_content TEXT,
  message_time TIMESTAMP,
  event_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES quantum_communication_events(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_network_devices (
  device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name VARCHAR(255),
  device_type VARCHAR(100),
  participant_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (participant_id) REFERENCES quantum_participants(participant_id)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_communication_events (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_time TIMESTAMP,
    sender VARCHAR(50),
    receiver VARCHAR(50),
    message TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_devices (
    device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    device_name VARCHAR(50),
    location VARCHAR(50),
    owner VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_protocols (
    protocol_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protocol_name VARCHAR(50),
    protocol_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_circuits (
    circuit_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_name VARCHAR(50),
    circuit_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_errors (
    error_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    error_type VARCHAR(50),
    error_description TEXT
)
